Attention all 7/8 grade volleyball players:

The Granite Ridge Conference has decided to allow 7/8 grade volleyball to have an “altered” fall season starting September 14th through October 9th. The season will include practice Monday – Thursday only at no charge. There will be no competition between schools. Please meet in the fieldhouse the first day of practice, right after school.

Please make sure your student has a current physical on file and is registered online before the first day of practice but DO NOT PAY (Choose “Pay Later”).

post_text:
Introducing Falcon Kids Care!

Falcon Kids Care is child care provided for students school-ages 5-12 enrolled in our district. We will have before and after school care as well as non-school day child care. Program availability is on a first-come, first-served basis; hence, early registration is strongly recommended. Governor declared Essential Workers, Tier 1, will have first priority (EO 20-82). This program will be fee based. The district is also allowed to accept families who are not Tier 1 workers. Wait lists will be created if needed.

Click the link for the following information:
https://www.foley.k12.mn.us/page/4248

Water Safety Instructor (WSI) is a Red Cross certification for swimming and diving instructors. The purpose of the course is to train instructor candidates to teach courses and presentations in the American Red Cross Swimming and Water Safety program by developing their understanding of how to use course materials, how to conduct training sessions, and how to evaluate participants' progress.

Participants must be 16 years old

This class will be held in person.
Masks are required during the in the classroom setting.
Please bring a water bottle, snacks, a pencil, pen, towel, swim suit.
August 21st: 8:00-6:00 pm
August 22nd: 8:00-6:00 pm
August 23rd: 12:00-4:00 pm

Class Fee: $255

Meet in the high school media center (enter door #1 of the high school (main entrance).

Babysitter Training, Ages 11+
Emergency Outfitters

This course follows the American Academy of Pediatrics-Babysitter Lessons and Safety Trainings (BLAST). Students will learn current practices for safety and injury prevention, first aid basics, feeding and caring for infants, how to handle behavior problems and how to manage their babysitting business. Students will receive a reference book, recipe and game handouts, babysitting bag and first aid kit. Please bring snacks. Class Fee: $65

Wed, August 26th • FIS Room 305 (6th grade pod)
Enter main entrance of intermediate school

Students need to wear a mask
Please bring- snacks, lunch, water bottle, and pencil/pens

post_text:
Weekly Challenges- “Full Steam Ahead with 4-H”

4-H Staff from Benton, McLeod, Meeker, Sherburne, Stearns and Wright Counties have teamed up to design a fun weekly educational challenge activity for youth to participate in all summer long.

“Full STEAM Ahead With 4-H” Weekly Challenges contain activities that can be completed with your whole family using supplies that you should have on hand at home and are a great way to learn about and make some 4-H projects. The challenges will be located on the MN 4-H at Home Site for families to access. If you miss a week, you can look back and watch. A new activity will be released each week from June, through the end of August. We hope you will choose to participate.

Link to activities htpps://z.umn.edu/FULLSTEAM

post_text:
Celebrate the Class of 2020!

At the conclusion of the Commencement Ceremony on May 30th, the graduates of Foley High School’s Class of 2020 will parade from the northwest corner of campus onto County Road 43/Norman Ave. Come and celebrate the graduates by parking your vehicle on the west shoulder (southbound) side of the road. Park by 8:10 p.m. to ensure you are in place for the parade. The graduates will parade north from the school campus to the intersection of County Road 43/Norman Ave and 85th Street North. Signs, honking and celebrating will be encouraged while asking that both spectators and parade attendees respect social distancing and remain in vehicles.

Lunch with Leaders Opportunity Live!

Students, as you continue to prepare for College and Career readiness, we have an opportunity to listen to a live presentation via Zoom on Medical Laboratory Science on May 12 @ 11AM by Louise Millis, MS, MLS(ASCP)CM, Medical Laboratory Science Program Director, St Cloud State University. What is the role of a Medical Laboratory Scientist? How do you become a Medical Laboratory Scientist? How much does a Medical Laboratory Scientist make? You do not have to be attending St. Cloud State University. No need to sign up just hop on here https://minnstate.zoom.us/j/99189798854,

If you can't attend the live presentation it will be posted on the Foley High School/Guidance Office website https://www.foley.k12.mn.us/page/2758/custom/6231.

Friday May 1st is School Lunch Hero Day. The Child Nutrition Department of Foley Schools are Heroes everyday! I want to take this time to thank them for all of the work that they do. They make delicious lunches during school and even box lunches currently. We appreciate you each and every day and being here each and every day...thanks also to everyone for making these meals happen for our kiddos. There are many staff members that make this happen. We appreciate those heroes as well. THANK YOU!!!

Here are pictures of a day starting at 5:00am until 10:00am. We serve approximately 1450 breakfast meals and 1450 lunch meals.....Enjoy! We MISS YOU ALL!

post_text:
Governor Walz has ordered school closures by Wednesday March 18, 2020 with a duration through March 27, 2020.

A decision ISD 51 Foley Public Schools will need to make is whether to hold school Monday and/or Tuesday March 16 and/or March 17.

Our administrative team will be meeting today at noon to discuss preliminary plans for Monday and Tuesday and our goal is to have a decision made and communication to you at 2:30 p.m. today.

This message is intended to go out to all parents and students so you may receive multiple messages.

Thank you
Paul Neubauer
Superintendent of Schools
Foley Public Schools

shared_text:
Foley Public Schools added 8 new photos.
March 9 at 2:46 PM ·

Ms. Monroe’s High School Spanish I students just completed a big project! It's a great compilation of what they've learned to date where they created coloring book pages and brought in crayons, toothbrushes, puzzles, cars, etc. to donate. To date our high school kids collected over 3,500 crayons, 51 toothbrushes, 45 health related items, 59 note pads, 92 writing utensils, 37 sheets of stickers, 32 cars, 9 pairs of sunglasses, 50 educational toys, and over 100 coloring books! In the next couple of weeks, Ms. Monroe will be bringing the coloring books and items to a group from St. Cloud that is traveling to Guatemala for a volunteer work opportunity installing stoves and water purifiers in homes and communities. The items our Foley students made and donated will be passed out to children throughout their trip.

Ms. Monroe’s 8th grade Spanish students are just starting this project.

Foley Public Schools added 41 new photos.
March 4 at 6:28 PM ·

This week was National Breakfast Week "School Breakfast out of this WORLD!
Students got to enjoy some time with Foley Fire Department, Officer Katie, Sheriff Troy Heck and Board Member Sharon Kipka. Thank you all so much for coming in and sharing time with us. It is amazing how the hot oatmeal with fixings, refrigerator oats with fruit and yogurt and French Toast were enjoyed. Eating breakfast is so important. It is served daily at Foley Public Schools.
